- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and dialog systems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel architecture for task-oriented dialog agents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed architecture uses attention mechanisms, which are a popular technique in machine learning. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the proposed architecture uses neural networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with developing a scalable dialog state tracking system.
